issue.title: add support for `deprecated` parameter

labels.name: enhancement
labels.description: New feature or request

issue.body: ### Is your feature request related to a problem? [OpenApi 3.0.3](https://swagger.io/specification/#schema-object) allows for a parameter `deprecated` in the schema object but the extension does not seem to use it. ### Describe the solution you'd like Property name could be crossed out and word "deprecated" can be used somewhere next to it, preferably in a colour that stands out. ### Describe alternatives you've considered Technically, it could be handled by the description: ```json "description": "deprecated User's email", ``` but since the schema actually allows for `deprecated` using it seems cleaner.

comment.body: Hi @maciekpitucha, thanks for the feature request. I think we should be able to adapt a solution based on how we mark properties as "required".

labels.name: documentation
labels.description: Improvements or additions to documentation

labels.name: enhancement
labels.description: New feature or request

labels.name: help wanted
labels.description: Extra attention is needed

issue.body:
Hi,


## Documentation link

https://github.com/PaloAltoNetworks/docusaurus-openapi-docs

## Describe the problem

we would like to achieve a functionality that is similar to the one that you present here:

https://docusaurus-openapi.tryingpan.dev/petstore/add-pet

We are starting by the following Open API documentation:

https://qanswer-core1.univ-st-etienne.fr/v2/api-docs

The problem is that we do not get the whole right part, send API request + code snippets.

At the beginning we thought they would be generated from the swagger documentation, but you start from 

https://github.com/PaloAltoNetworks/docusaurus-openapi-docs/blob/main/demo/examples/petstore.yaml

which already contains the code snippets. Is this right? How can we achieve a similar input file? I would try to imporve the documentation to indicate this to users .... 

## Suggested fix

comment.body: Disregard, after further testing it also works simply by including the `api` frontmatter and using `ApiItem` to render the doc. That said, we'll need to think more about how to support the use case you brought up.

issue.title: add support for `deprecated` parameter

labels.name: enhancement
labels.description: New feature or request

issue.body: ### Is your feature request related to a problem? [OpenApi 3.0.3](https://swagger.io/specification/#schema-object) allows for a parameter `deprecated` in the schema object but the extension does not seem to use it. ### Describe the solution you'd like Property name could be crossed out and word "deprecated" can be used somewhere next to it, preferably in a colour that stands out. ### Describe alternatives you've considered Technically, it could be handled by the description: ```json "description": "deprecated User's email", ``` but since the schema actually allows for `deprecated` using it seems cleaner.

comment.body: Hi @maciekpitucha, thanks for the feature request. I think we should be able to adapt a solution based on how we mark properties as "required".

labels.name: documentation
labels.description: Improvements or additions to documentation

labels.name: enhancement
labels.description: New feature or request

labels.name: help wanted
labels.description: Extra attention is needed

issue.body:
Hi,


## Documentation link

https://github.com/PaloAltoNetworks/docusaurus-openapi-docs

## Describe the problem

we would like to achieve a functionality that is similar to the one that you present here:

https://docusaurus-openapi.tryingpan.dev/petstore/add-pet

We are starting by the following Open API documentation:

https://qanswer-core1.univ-st-etienne.fr/v2/api-docs

The problem is that we do not get the whole right part, send API request + code snippets.

At the beginning we thought they would be generated from the swagger documentation, but you start from 

https://github.com/PaloAltoNetworks/docusaurus-openapi-docs/blob/main/demo/examples/petstore.yaml

which already contains the code snippets. Is this right? How can we achieve a similar input file? I would try to imporve the documentation to indicate this to users .... 

## Suggested fix

comment.body: Disregard, after further testing it also works simply by including the `api` frontmatter and using `ApiItem` to render the doc. That said, we'll need to think more about how to support the use case you brought up.

[OpenApi 3.0.3](https://swagger.io/specification/#schema-object) allows for a parameter `deprecated` in the schema object but the extension does not seem to use it. ### Describe the solution you'd like Property name could be crossed out and word "deprecated" can be used somewhere next to it, preferably in a colour that stands out. ### Describe alternatives you've considered Technically, it could be handled by the description: ```json "description": "deprecated User's email", ``` but since the schema actually allows for `deprecated` using it seems cleaner.

comment.body: Hi @maciekpitucha, thanks for the feature request. I think we should be able to adapt a solution based on how we mark properties as "required".

issue.body:
Hi,


## Documentation link

https://github.com/PaloAltoNetworks/docusaurus-openapi-docs

## Describe the problem

we would like to achieve a functionality that is similar to the one that you present here:

https://docusaurus-openapi.tryingpan.dev/petstore/add-pet

We are starting by the following Open API documentation:

https://qanswer-core1.univ-st-etienne.fr/v2/api-docs

The problem is that we do not get the whole right part, send API request + code snippets.

At the beginning we thought they would be generated from the swagger documentation, but you start from 

https://github.com/PaloAltoNetworks/docusaurus-openapi-docs/blob/main/demo/examples/petstore.yaml

which already contains the code snippets. Is this right? How can we achieve a similar input file? I would try to imporve the documentation to indicate this to users .... 

## Suggested fix

comment.body: Disregard, after further testing it also works simply by including the `api` frontmatter and using `ApiItem` to render the doc. That said, we'll need to think more about how to support the use case you brought up.
